						<summary>

						<p>This records an endowment of 2000 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land at Śiṟṟiyāṟṟūr in Mēl-Paḷugūr-nāḍu a division of Maṇaiyil-kōṭṭam, left in charge of the <hi rend="italic">Vaishṇavadāsar</hi> managing the temple of Gōvindapāḍi-Perumānaḍigaḷ by Mannaṉ Kaṇṇaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kāmarmōha-Vāraṇappēraraiyar the elephant <hi rend="italic">mahout</hi> of the king, for the purpose of feeding one Brāhmaṇa daily in the <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> (attached to the temple). The land is said to have been purchased by the donor from the temple itself.</p>						

						</summary>
